snippet.textDisplay: As far as I am also hyped for this, I just feel sad ( and ultimately worried) that going back to the MW title over and over seems to be the only way that Activision can get people to be interested in Call Of Duty again.  Remember when CODs other than MWs brought us Gun Game, Zombies, Nuketown, actual gore and dismemberment, choices and consequences during campaigns? From MWR to new MW to MW2R, is profiting from something that was created 13 years ago the only way that the franchise can stay alive at this point?
snippet.textOriginal: As far as I am also hyped for this, I just feel sad ( and ultimately worried) that going back to the MW title over and over seems to be the only way that Activision can get people to be interested in Call Of Duty again.
